    <refnamediv>
        <refname>gl_PatchVerticesIn</refname>
        <refpurpose>contains the number of vertices in the current patch</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv><title>Declaration</title>
        <funcsynopsis>
            <function>in int gl_PatchVerticesIn;</function>
        </funcsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsect1 id="description"><title>Description</title>
        <para>
            Available only in the tessellation control and evaluation languages, <function>gl_PatchVerticesIn</function>
            contains the number of vertices in the input being processed by the shader. A single tessellation control or
            evaluation shader can read patches of differing sizes, and so th value of <function>gl_PatchVertexIn</function>
            may differ between patches.
        </para>
    </refsect1>
